      "content": "That's an interesting distinction. For Defendant B, you mentioned his environment suggests a lack of support structures which leads to \"problematic behavior.\" Are you saying that his background makes him inherently more likely to re-offend compared to Defendant A? How much weight would a judge typically give to those environmental \"aggravating factors\" versus the specific nature of the crime?",
